    "methodology": "Formal volunteering is defined as unpaid help given through groups, clubs or organisations at least once in the last 12 months. Informal volunteering is unpaid help given as an individual to people who are not relatives at least once in the last 12 months. Regular volunteering is at least once a week. The Community Life Survey is a household survey of adults aged 16+ in England with a sample of approximately 10,000 respondents. Age-group breakdowns are drawn from published cross-tabulations. The survey moved to mixed-mode (online and telephone) in 2020-21, which may affect comparability with earlier face-to-face fieldwork.",
